    • Constructor Detail

      • AXmlNode

        public AXmlNode(String tag,
                String ns,
                AXmlNode parent)
        Creates a new AXmlNode object with the given tag, namespace and parent.
        Keep in mind that this node will automatically be added as child to the given parent node with parent.addChild(this). If you want to create a root node you can set parent to null.
        The addded flag is defaulted to true (see AXmlElement.added).
        Parameters:
        tag - the node's tag.
        ns - the node's namespace.
        parent - the node's parent node.

      • AXmlNode

        public AXmlNode(String tag,
                String ns,
                AXmlNode parent,
                boolean added)
        Creates a new AXmlNode object with the given tag, namespace and parent. Keep in mind that this node will automatically be added as child to the given parent node with parent.addChild(this).
        Parameters:
        tag - the node's tag.
        ns - the node's namespace.
        parent - the node's parent node.
        added - wheter this node was part of a parsed xml file or added afterwards.
